      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is bulk content generation?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Producing large volumes of content using AI tools instead of manual writing. Output includes blog articles, product descriptions, social posts, landing pages, and email sequences. Tools generate 25 to 1,000+ pieces monthly, prioritizing volume without proportionally scaling teams or budgets.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Google penalize bulk AI content?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Google penalizes low-quality content, not AI content specifically. The risk is accidentally publishing thin content at scale. Quality control matters more than generation method. Edit top performers, delete underperformers after 90 days.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many articles per month is considered bulk?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Most teams consider 30+ articles monthly as bulk production. Freelancers produce 4–8 per month; small teams produce 12–20. Bulk tools range from 25 at entry to 1,000+. The right volume depends on your niche, keyword opportunity, and quality requirements.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I use bulk content generators for product descriptions?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, some tools support this. Writesonic, Copy.ai, ContentBot, and Jasper generate product descriptions. Writesonic is strongest for e-commerce with Shopify integration. Byword, Autoblogging.ai, SEOWriting.ai, and Article Forge handle blog articles only.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the cheapest bulk content tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Article Forge at $13/month for 25 articles ($0.52/article). SEOWriting.ai at $14/month for 50 articles ($0.28/article). At scale, Article Forge at $57/month for 500 articles costs $0.11/article. Quality correlates with price — cheaper tools require more editing.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Should I use a bulk content tool or hire writers?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Both serve different purposes. Bulk tools excel at informational long-tail articles, product descriptions, and social posts where volume matters. Writers excel at thought leadership and competitive keywords requiring depth. Use bulk tools for 80% of content, writers for 20% of strategic authority pieces.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between bulk content generation and autoblogging?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
